<p>The Last Of Us Part 2	</p>

<p>A heart-wrenching story. Much like part 1, The last of us part 2 is a story with no classic good guys/bad guys. Everyone is a person with a relatable backstory, desires, regrets, and hopes. The thing is, they do not align, leading to people crossing each other's path a way noone wants them to. The producers have outdone themselves, telling a non-linear story with flashbacks that hit hard, and at the perfect time. SPOILERS AHEAD!!!!
</p>

<p>The story starts with Joel on a relaxing scouting mission with his brother Tommy, signaling that Joel and Ellie had arrived at the Jackson community safely, and they are having a closest-to-normal life there in an apocalypse. Joel told Tommy the story, that he and Ellie set out to seek the Firefly group for a purpose: creating the vaccine for humanity.
They found them in Salt Lake city. The doctors there were hopeful at the prospect of saving humanity, ending this fungal nightmare once and for all. The only catch? The surgery would have killed Ellie. 
</p>
<p>""
</p>




										

